#Text=Wait until you see the statues of the young athletes in the Museum ,  he cried , enthusiastically , " and get a glimpse of the blue sky back of Mount Hymettus , and the moonlight some evening on the Acropolis , and you 'll be convinced that nothing counts for much in this world but health and straight limbs , and tall marble pillars , and eyes trained to see only what is beautiful .

column1: #Text=Give people a love for beauty and a respect for health , Miss Morris , and the result is going to be , what they once had here , the best art and the greatest writers and satirists and poets .

#Text=The same audience that applauded Euripides and Sophocles in the open theatre used to cross the road the same day to applaud the athletes who ran naked in the Olympian games , and gave them as great honor .

#Text=I came here once on a walking tour with a chap who was n't making as much of himself as he should have done , and he went away a changed man , and became a personage in the world , and you would never guess what it was that did it .

#Text=He saw a statue of one of the Greek gods in the Museum which showed certain muscles that he could n't find in his own body , and he told me he was going to train down until they did show ; and he stopped drinking and loafing to do it , and took to exercising and working ; and by the time the muscles showed out clear and strong he was so keen over life that he wanted to make the most of it , and , as I said , he has done it .
#Text=That 's what a respect for his own body did for him .

#Text= exclaimed Carlton ; " I should say so !

column1: #Text=The last time I was here I tried to wear a pair of knickerbockers around the city , and the people stared so that I had to go back to the hotel and change them .

#Text=I should n't have minded it so much in any other country , but I thought men who wore Jaeger underclothing and women 's petticoats for a national costume might have excused so slight an eccentricity as knickerbockers .
#Text=THEY had no right to throw the first stone .
